
// This code snippet uses the [or] slot to evaluate two conditions: whether the value of the [stream] argument is false using [eq], or if the [stream] argument does not exist using [not-exists]. The [or] slot returns true if either condition is met, allowing for logical branching based on the presence and value of the [stream] argument.
or
   eq:x:@.arguments/*/stream
      .:bool:false
   not-exists:x:@.arguments/*/stream
